<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Leader" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Leader,</orth> 1) one who leads, directs the steps, shows the way: <cit><quote>these mine eyes, true --s to their queen,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 503" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 503</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>you were wont to be a follower, but now you are a l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 2, 3</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) commander, captain: <bibl n="shak. luc 296" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 296</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.1.118" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 1, 118</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.68" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 2, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.68" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 2, 68</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.1.25" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.2.99" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 99</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.143" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 143</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.32" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.3.17" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 2, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.25" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 3, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.232" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 232</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.7.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 7, 70</bibl>. Used of those who give directions in a dance: <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.157" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 157</bibl>. of the queen-bee: <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.126" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 126</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>